\begin{abstract}
In this paper we investigate the spectral expansion for the asymptotically
spectral differential operators generated in $L_{2}^{m}(-\infty,\infty)$ by
ordinary differential expression of arbitrary order with periodic
matrix-valued coefficients.

Key Words: Periodic nonself-adjoint differential operator, Spectral
singularities, Spectral expansion.

AMS Mathematics Subject Classification: 34L05, 34L20.

\end{abstract}

